Using the car prices dataset that can be found here containing 26 features such as car name, number of doors, and engine size, and 204 instances of those features, I predict the car price.
The first few feature distributions looks like this;
  The distribution of the car prices looks like a log-normal distribution, as can be see below;
  I perfomed some exploratory data anylsis to get a feel of the data and its features, for example a good feature to predict price is engine size.

Eco Spatial Solutions is a project to meet the objectives of the Plan Melbourne 2017-2050 project, which is a long-term plan devised to facilitate sustainable development in Melbourne’s growing future.
This project provides a solution to the Direction 6.7 of the Plan, i.e. to;
 Improve the economic recovery of waste and reduce reliance on landfill Improve waste and resource recovery systems to meet the logistical challenges of medium and higher density developments Protect waste management and resource recovery facilities from urban encroachment and assess opportunities for new waste facilities  motivation
